abstract: The Dow Jones industrial average fell 119.48 points as investors digested gloomy numbers on sales of new homes and were unmoved by a report that showed a rise in United States durable goods orders.
snippet: The Dow Jones industrial average fell 119.48 points as investors digested gloomy numbers on sales of new homes and were unmoved by a report that showed a rise in United States durable goods orders.
lead_paragraph: Stocks fell on Wednesday as investors digested gloomy numbers on sales of new homes and were unmoved by a report that showed a rise in United States durable goods orders.

headline.main: Weak Home Sales Trump Strength in Durable Goods
